text: I don't know who authorizes movie trailers these days, but they should be fired at this point. This trailer kinda killed the movie for me. The first half of the trailer was great: You have this lone wolf who's identity is a mystery. Her presence is a threat, and she has tamed dragons. You get the sense that she'd be the villain. Thats the way it should have been in the trailer. That way when you go see the movie you have this thing that films used to utilize, called suspense. The reveal would have been a good plot twist, but it was ruined in the tailer. Im so sick of film trailers showing 90% more than they need too. Trailers are supposed to tease the audience, they're supposed to leave the audience wanting to know more. How am I supposed to want to know more when you tell me every damn plot device in the film?
